<HEAD>Former Tunisian President Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Habib Bourguiba, ousted
from power in November 1987, entered a hospital in Tunis today for
prostate surgery, medical sources reported.
   The sources said the operation would be conducted by a French
specialist, who was not named, assisted by Tunisian doctors.
   Bourguiba, 86, was ousted by Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali on Nov. 7,
1987 in a bloodless coup.
   Ben Ali, now president, said Bourguiba was removed because he had
become senile and physically incapable of performing the duties of
president.
   Until the ouster, Bourguiba was the only president Tunisia had
ever had since independence from France in 1956.
