<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--SAfrica-Executions     07-18 0135</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--SAfrica-Executions,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Men Hanged for Murder, Bringing Year's Executions To 37</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three black men were hanged
today for the murder of a white man in a black township, bringing to
37 the number of executions in South Africa this year, the Ministry
of Justice said.
   Spokeswoman Marie Pienaar said Joseph Lebeloane, Joseph Manyane
and Simon Selepe were executed in Pretoria prison. They had been
convicted of robbing and murdering their victim in July 1986 after
meeting him in a night club in Katlehong, east of Johannesburg.
   The rate of executions is down this year from 1988, when 117
people were hanged, and 1987, when 164 were executed.
   Those executed this year include 28 black men and two white men,
six men of mixed race and one mixed-race woman.
</TEXT>
