<HEAD>Thunderstorms From Louisiana to Dakotas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms continued over the nation's midsection this morning
after producing damaging winds, heavy rains and hail as big as
baseballs from Louisiana to the Dakotas.
   Winds gusted to 60 mph at Atlantic, Iowa, Foreman, Ark., Fremont,
Neb. and near Sioux Falls, S.D., late Monday. There were about two
dozen reports of wind damage in southern Arkansas, southeast
Oklahoma, the northern two thirds of Louisiana and west-central
Mississippi.
   In Nebraska, baseball-size hail fell at Wellfleet, and Farnam was
pelted with hail the size of golf balls and deluged with more than
1\ inches of rain in 15 minutes.
   Three-quarter inch hail fell at several locations in Kansas.
   Heavier rainfall during the 6 hours ended at 2 a.m. EDT included
2 inches at Sioux City, Iowa; 1{ inches at Omaha and 1.39 inches at
Norfolk, Neb.; and more than three quarters of an inch at Sioux
Falls, S.D.
