Virginia and North Carolina, and scattered over Florida and Georgia.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the
upper Great Lakes and upper Mississippi Valley across the middle
Mississippi and lower Missouri valleys into Oklahoma and Arkansas.
Storms were likely to become severe from southeast Kansas into parts
of Oklahoma, Missouri and Arkansas. Scattered showers and
thunderstorms were forecast from the eastern Carolinas to the
Florida Peninsula.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s over the upper Great Lakes
and upper Mississippi Valley, across northwest Washington State and
eastern Maine; between 100 and 110 degrees from the California
interior through much of Arizona and New Mexico into southwest and
central Texas; and between 110 and 115 degrees over the Desert
Southwest. Highs elsewhere generally were expected to be in the 80s
and 90s.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 43 degrees at Yellowstone,
Wyo., to 96 degrees at Phoenix.
