<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-ConAgra     07-18 0246</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-ConAgra,0256</SECOND>
<HEAD>ConAgra Reports Record Fourth Quarter, Full Year Sales, Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Food conglomerate ConAgra Inc. said Tuesday
its fourth quarter profit rose 42 percent from a year earlier.
   The company said it earned $65.4 million, or 80 cents per share,
in the three months ended May 28, compared with $46.2 million, or 58
cents per share, in the previous year.
   Fourth-quarter revenue rose to $2.97 billion from $2.6 billion.
   ConAgra in June agreed to terminate a lengthy takeover battle
against Tyson Foods Inc. for Holly Farms Corp., one of the nation's
biggest poultry processors. ConAgra, which earlier had reached a
merger agreement with Holly Farms that was challenged by Tyson, will
receive $50 million from the companies for agreeing to drop out of
the bidding.
   For the full year, net income rose 28 percent to $197.9 million,
or $2.45 a share, from $154.7 million, or $1.94 a share, a year
earlier.
   Full-year sales gained 18 percent to $11.34 billion from $9.61
billion.
   In ConAgra's largest industry segment, Prepared Foods, operating
profit increased 43 percent to $293.1 million in fiscal 1989 from
$205 million in 1988. Sales increased 15 percent to $7.08 billion
from $6.13 billion.
   ConAgra is one of the nation's biggest food and agricultural
companies, selling poultry, frozen foods, processed meats, pet food,
fertilizer and animal feed under brand names that include Armour,
Banquet and Country Pride. The company also has major interests in
grain processing, finance and international trading.
</TEXT>
